The course gives an overview of the aim and content of the topic "Me and the environment" as well as  of  its educational activities, teaching methods and possibilities of implementing them in practice. Theoretical matierials are supported by practical work, illustrations, examples and guidance.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give necessary knowledge and didactical and practical skills to teach the topic "Me and the environment" at pre-school.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of the course a student  1) will know the aim, content and principles of educational activities for the theme "Me and the enviornment" and can use them for planning both indoor and outdoor activities as well as in composing  study materials: 2) will have  an overview of methods to teach the topic "Me and the enviornment"; 3) will know how to integrate the content and teaching activities with other subjects, considering general educational principles; 4) will know how to observe objects in nature using suitable observation techniques; 5) know how to build a simple nature trail;  6) can  make observation guides and activity plans; 7) will practice  different activities.
